.TH "comedi_pci_auto_config" 9 "comedi_pci_auto_config" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
comedi_pci_auto_config \- Configure/probe a PCI COMEDI device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" comedi_pci_auto_config
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pcidev "  ","
.BI "struct comedi_driver *driver "  ","
.BI "unsigned long context "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pcidev" 12
PCI device.
.IP "driver" 12
Registered COMEDI driver.
.IP "context" 12
Driver specific data, passed to \fBcomedi_auto_config\fP.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Typically called from the pci_driver (*probe) function.  Auto-configure
a COMEDI device, using the \fIstruct device\fP embedded in *\fIpcidev\fP as the
hardware device.  The \fIcontext\fP value gets passed through to \fIdriver\fP's
"auto_attach" handler.  The "auto_attach" handler may call
\fBcomedi_to_pci_dev\fP on the passed in COMEDI device to recover \fIpcidev\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
The result of calling \fBcomedi_auto_config\fP (0 on success, or
a negative error number on failure).
